{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ridt9FPsfSuyMKMzddcvoS","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the orchestration flow. Let me create a final summary document with all the key information.\n\n## Summary: Cloche Orchestration Flow\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase. Here's the complete picture of how orchestration works:\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\n**Three binaries from one Go module:**\n1. **`cloche`** — CLI client (short-lived, talks to daemon over gRPC)\n2. **`cloched`** — Daemon (long-running, manages container lifecycle and executes host workflows)\n3. **`cloche-agent`** — In-container entrypoint (autonomous agent that walks workflow graphs)\n\n---\n\n### Core Domain Types\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/`\n\n**Key types:**\n- **`domain.Workflow`** — Workflow definition with steps, wiring, and collects\n  - `Name`: workflow identifier\n  - `Location`: `LocationHost` or `LocationContainer` (enum)\n  - `Steps`: map of step name → `*domain.Step`\n  - `Wiring`: slice of `Wire` (connects step results to next steps)\n  - `Collects`: conditional fanin (merge multiple branches)\n  - `EntryStep`: initial step to launch\n  - `Config`: workflow-level config (e.g., `host.agent_command`)\n\n- **`domain.Step`** — Individual workflow step\n  - `Name`: unique step ID\n  - `Type`: `StepTypeAgent`, `StepTypeScript`, or `StepTypeWorkflow`\n  - `Results`: declared result names (e.g., `[\"success\", \"fail\"]`)\n  - `Config`: step-level config map (e.g., `run`, `prompt`, `workflow_name`)\n\n- **`domain.Run`** — Execution record\n  - `ID`: unique run identifier (e.g., `develop-bold-oak`)\n  - `WorkflowName`: which workflow was run\n  - `State`: `RunStatePending`, `RunStateRunning`, `RunStateSucceeded`, `RunStateFailed`, `RunStateCancelled`\n  - `ActiveSteps`: currently executing steps\n  - `StepExecutions`: slice of `StepExecution` (captures timing, result, logs)\n  - `IsHost`: boolean flag (true for host workflow runs)\n  - `ParentRunID`: for child container runs, points to parent host run\n  - `BaseSHA`: git HEAD at run start (for branch creation)\n\n---\n\n### Orchestration Loop: Host Workflows\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n**The `Loop` implements a continuous orchestration loop** that keeps up to `MaxConcurrent` host workflow runs active:\n\n```go\ntype Loop struct {\n    config   LoopConfig\n    runner   RunFunc                     // function to launch a host workflow run\n    store    ports.RunStore\n    assigner TaskAssigner               // optional; queries external task source\n    stopCh   chan struct{}\n    dedup    map[string]time.Time        // task ID → last assignment time (prevents reassignment)\n}\n```\n\n**Key configuration:**\n- `MaxConcurrent`: how many host runs to keep active (default 1)\n- `StaggerDelay`: delay between launching consecutive runs\n- `DedupTimeout`: how long to suppress reassignment (default 5 min)\n\n**Loop algorithm** (`loop.run()`):\n1. **Fill slots**: While `inFlight < MaxConcurrent`:\n   - Check active host runs from store\n   - Optional: pick a task ID from `TaskAssigner` (with dedup filtering)\n   - Launch a new `Runner` goroutine\n2. **Wait for completions**: Listen on `completions` channel\n   - If succeeded: immediately try to fill slots again (no backoff)\n   - If failed: back off for `idlePollInterval` (30s) before retry\n3. **No tasks**: If task assigner returns no tasks, back off\n\n**Polling intervals:**\n- `idlePollInterval = 30s` (wait when no work available)\n- `capacityPollInterval = 5s` (wait when at capacity)\n- `defaultDedupTimeout = 5m` (task dedup window)\n\n---\n\n### Host Workflow Executor\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\nThe `Executor` implements `engine.StepExecutor` for host workflow steps:\n\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MainDir       string              // main branch worktree dir\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher        // dispatches container workflows\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    OutputDir     string               // .cloche/<run-id>/output\n    Wires         []domain.Wire\n    HostRunID     string               // parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string             // fallback agent command chain\n    AgentArgs     []string\n    TaskID        string               // daemon-assigned task ID\n}\n```\n\n**Step execution by type:**\n\n1. **Script step** (`run` config key)\n   - Executes shell command via `exec.Command`\n   - Exit 0 → `success`; non-zero → `fail` (or look for result marker in output)\n   - Environment: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, plus output mappings\n   - Output written to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n\n2. **Workflow step** (`workflow_name` config key)\n   - Reads prompt from previous step's output (or `prompt_step` override)\n   - Calls `Dispatcher.RunWorkflow()` → returns child run ID\n   - Links child run to parent via `ParentRunID`\n   - **Polls** the store (2s interval) until child run reaches terminal state\n   - Child's `succeeded` → `success`; `failed`/`cancelled` → `fail`\n\n3. **Agent step** (`prompt` config key)\n   - Uses prompt adapter (at `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`)\n   - Reads previous step output as prompt\n   - Invokes agent command on host\n   - Output captured and stored\n\n**Key helper functions:**\n- `resolveOutputMappings()`: extracts values from previous step output using JSON paths\n- `waitForRun()`: polls store until run is terminal\n- `findPrevOutput()`: locates previous step output for data flow\n- `stepOutputPath()`: returns file path for step output\n- `MainWorktreeDir()`: finds the main git worktree (for script execution context)\n\n---\n\n### Host Workflow Runner\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n\nThe `Runner` is the entry point for executing host workflows:\n\n```go\ntype Runner struct {\n    Dispatcher RunDispatcher          // to dispatch container workflows\n    Store      ports.RunStore\n    TaskID     string                 // optional task ID from daemon loop\n}\n\n// Run parses .cloche/host.cloche and executes the \"main\" workflow\nfunc (r *Runner) Run(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) (*RunResult, error)\n\n// RunWithID allows specifying a custom run ID\nfunc (r *Runner) RunWithID(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, runID string) (*RunResult, error)\n```\n\n**Execution flow:**\n1. Read `.cloche/host.cloche`\n2. Parse with `dsl.ParseForHost()` → validates as host workflow\n3. Verify workflow name is `\"main\"`\n4. Create output directory: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n5. Create `domain.Run` record and persist to store\n6. Create an `Executor` and pass to `engine.New()`\n7. Run the workflow through the execution engine\n8. Persist final state to store\n\n**Status handler** (`hostStatusHandler`):\n- Logs step start/complete events\n- Updates `domain.Run` with step execution details\n- Called by the execution engine at key points\n\n---\n\n### Workflow Execution Engine\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\nThe `Engine` is workflow-agnostic and drives step execution:\n\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor        // host executor or container executor\n    status         StatusHandler       // callback interface for events\n    maxSteps       int                 // default 1000\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration       // default 30 min per step\n}\n\n// Run executes a workflow, returns terminal domain.Run or error\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n**Algorithm:**\n1. Validate workflow (all results wired, all steps reachable)\n2. Launch entry step in a goroutine\n3. **Main event loop**: listen for step completions\n   - Validate result is declared\n   - Record completion in `domain.Run`\n   - Process wiring: get next targets via `wf.NextSteps(stepName, result)`\n   - Fanout: launch all target steps in parallel\n   - Handle `done` (success) and `abort` (fail) terminals\n   - Check `Collect` conditions (fanin: merge multiple branches)\n4. When all branches complete → determine final state\n\n**Collects** (fanin):\n- `CollectAll`: fire when ALL conditions are satisfied\n- `CollectAny`: fire when ANY condition is satisfied\n- Can target a step or terminal (`done`/`abort`)\n\n**Step timeout:**\n- Read from `step.Config[\"timeout\"]`\n- Fallback to engine's `defaultTimeout` (30 min)\n- Applied per step via `context.WithTimeout()`\n\n---\n\n### Daemon Integration\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\n**Startup flow:**\n1. Load global config (`~/.config/cloche/config`)\n2. Initialize SQLite store\n3. **Sweep stale runs** from previous daemon crash\n4. Initialize container runtime (Docker or local)\n5. Create gRPC server with:\n   - Store\n   - Container runtime\n   - Default image\n   - Log broadcaster\n   - Evolution trigger (optional)\n6. Call `autoRunActiveProjects()` for each project with `active: true` in config\n   - Launches a `Runner` in a goroutine for each active project's host workflow\n7. Listen on gRPC socket (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n\n**gRPC Server** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`):\n- `RunWorkflow(req)`: Dispatch a container workflow\n  - Generate unique run ID\n  - Write prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (if provided)\n  - Persist `domain.Run` to store\n  - Launch container **in background** (returns immediately)\n  - Container tracks completion asynchronously\n- Maintains `loops` map: `project_dir → *host.Loop`\n\n**Container workflow dispatch:**\n- `launchAndTrack()` runs in background goroutine\n- Ensures image is up-to-date (optional `ImageEnsurer`)\n- Calls `container.Start()` → container ID\n- Attaches to container output (JSON-lines status messages)\n- Tracks container exit status\n- Extracts results to git branches\n- Updates `domain.Run` state\n\n---\n\n### DSL Parsing\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\n**Workflow DSL format:**\n```\nworkflow \"name\" {\n  step step-name {\n    run = \"shell command\"               # OR\n    prompt = file(\"path/to/prompt\")     # OR\n    workflow_name = \"container-wf\"      # host.cloche only\n    results = [success, fail, ...]\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    timeout = \"10m\"\n  }\n\n  # Wiring (fan-out)\n  source-step:result -> target-step\n  source-step:result -> done\n  source-step:result -> abort\n\n  # Collect (fan-in)\n  collect all(step1:result1, step2:result2) -> target-step\n  collect any(step1:result1, step2:result2) -> target-step\n\n  # Workflow-level config\n  container {\n    image = \"my-image:latest\"\n  }\n\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n    agent_args = \"--model opus\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step type inference:**\n- Presence of `run` key → `StepTypeScript`\n- Presence of `prompt` key → `StepTypeAgent`\n- Presence of `workflow_name` key → `StepTypeWorkflow` (host.cloche only)\n\n**Parser validation:**\n- Every result must be wired (via `Wire` or `Collect`)\n- Every step must be reachable from entry step\n- No duplicate env var mappings in wires\n- Location-based validation: `workflow_name` disallowed in container workflows\n\n---\n\n### Ports (Interfaces)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n\n**`ports.RunStore`** — Persist run records\n- `CreateRun()`, `GetRun()`, `UpdateRun()`, `DeleteRun()`\n- `ListRuns()`, `ListRunsByProject()`, `ListProjects()`\n- `ListChildRuns()` (for parent-child relationships)\n\n**`ports.CaptureStore`** — Persist step execution details\n- `SaveCapture()`, `GetCaptures()`\n\n**`ports.ContainerRuntime`** — Manage containers\n- `Start()`, `Stop()`, `Wait()`, `Inspect()`\n- `AttachOutput()`, `CopyFrom()`, `Logs()`, `Remove()`\n- Optional: `ImageEnsurer.EnsureImage()`\n\n**`ports.LogStore`** — Index extracted log files\n- `SaveLogFile()`, `GetLogFiles()`, `GetLogFilesByStep()`, `GetLogFileByType()`\n\n---\n\n### Flow: Container Workflow Dispatch\n\n**When host executor runs a `workflow_name` step:**\n\n1. Host executor calls `Dispatcher.RunWorkflow(ctx, RunWorkflowRequest)`\n2. gRPC server handler:\n   - Generates unique run ID (workflow-specific format)\n   - Writes prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Creates `domain.Run` record in store\n   - Launches `launchAndTrack()` in background\n3. `launchAndTrack()`:\n   - Ensures image is built\n   - Calls `container.Start()` → container ID\n   - Updates `domain.Run` to running state\n   - Calls `trackRun()` to monitor container\n4. `trackRun()`:\n   - Attaches to container stdout (JSON-lines protocol)\n   - Parses step execution events\n   - Updates `domain.Run` with step completions\n   - On exit: copies results to git branches\n   - Updates final run state\n5. Host executor polls via `waitForRun()`:\n   - Queries store every 2 seconds\n   - Returns when child run reaches terminal state\n   - Maps `succeeded` → `success`, `failed`/`cancelled` → `fail`\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon entrypoint, initialization, auto-run active projects |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` | Orchestration loop: maintains max concurrent runs |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow entry point, parsing, execution |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Step executor for host workflows (script, workflow, agent) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` | `Task` model and `TaskAssigner` interface |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Generic workflow execution engine, wiring/collect logic |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | `Workflow`, `Step`, `Wire`, `Collect`, `OutputMapping` types |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | `Run`, `StepExecution`, run state management |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/namegen.go` | Human-readable run ID generation |\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` | Workflow DSL parsing |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC server, container dispatch, tracking |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | Interfaces: `RunStore`, `CaptureStore`, `LogStore`, `EvolutionStore` |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` | `ContainerRuntime`, `ContainerConfig`, `ImageEnsurer` |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go` | `AgentAdapter` interface |\n\n---\n\n### Design Document\n\nSee `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` for the comprehensive design of host workflows."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ae223074e4b614554 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59803\ntool_uses: 32\nduration_ms: 79019</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84afe276-0872-4aba-bc33-ed0e3777b6c9","uuid":"5eeaaf2e-0202-4585-8e5c-bc694bb24803","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Go project thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The current orchestration loop in the daemon (cloched) - how it currently works, the timed/capped loop approach\n2. The host workflow executor and how it runs host.cloche workflows\n3. The domain types: Workflow, Step, Result, Run\n4. The ports/interfaces: especially anything related to orchestration, run management\n5. How container workflow runs are dispatched\n6. The current host.cloche workflow format and how it's parsed/executed\n\nFocus on:\n- cmd/cloched/ - the daemon entry point\n- internal/host/ - host workflow executor\n- internal/domain/ - core types\n- internal/ports/ - interfaces\n- internal/adapters/ - implementations\n- Any test files related to orchestration\n\nGive me file paths, key types, key functions, and how the orchestration flow works end-to-end.","agentId":"ae223074e4b614554","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the orchestration flow. Let me create a final summary document with all the key information.\n\n## Summary: Cloche Orchestration Flow\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase. Here's the complete picture of how orchestration works:\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\n**Three binaries from one Go module:**\n1. **`cloche`** — CLI client (short-lived, talks to daemon over gRPC)\n2. **`cloched`** — Daemon (long-running, manages container lifecycle and executes host workflows)\n3. **`cloche-agent`** — In-container entrypoint (autonomous agent that walks workflow graphs)\n\n---\n\n### Core Domain Types\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/`\n\n**Key types:**\n- **`domain.Workflow`** — Workflow definition with steps, wiring, and collects\n  - `Name`: workflow identifier\n  - `Location`: `LocationHost` or `LocationContainer` (enum)\n  - `Steps`: map of step name → `*domain.Step`\n  - `Wiring`: slice of `Wire` (connects step results to next steps)\n  - `Collects`: conditional fanin (merge multiple branches)\n  - `EntryStep`: initial step to launch\n  - `Config`: workflow-level config (e.g., `host.agent_command`)\n\n- **`domain.Step`** — Individual workflow step\n  - `Name`: unique step ID\n  - `Type`: `StepTypeAgent`, `StepTypeScript`, or `StepTypeWorkflow`\n  - `Results`: declared result names (e.g., `[\"success\", \"fail\"]`)\n  - `Config`: step-level config map (e.g., `run`, `prompt`, `workflow_name`)\n\n- **`domain.Run`** — Execution record\n  - `ID`: unique run identifier (e.g., `develop-bold-oak`)\n  - `WorkflowName`: which workflow was run\n  - `State`: `RunStatePending`, `RunStateRunning`, `RunStateSucceeded`, `RunStateFailed`, `RunStateCancelled`\n  - `ActiveSteps`: currently executing steps\n  - `StepExecutions`: slice of `StepExecution` (captures timing, result, logs)\n  - `IsHost`: boolean flag (true for host workflow runs)\n  - `ParentRunID`: for child container runs, points to parent host run\n  - `BaseSHA`: git HEAD at run start (for branch creation)\n\n---\n\n### Orchestration Loop: Host Workflows\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n**The `Loop` implements a continuous orchestration loop** that keeps up to `MaxConcurrent` host workflow runs active:\n\n```go\ntype Loop struct {\n    config   LoopConfig\n    runner   RunFunc                     // function to launch a host workflow run\n    store    ports.RunStore\n    assigner TaskAssigner               // optional; queries external task source\n    stopCh   chan struct{}\n    dedup    map[string]time.Time        // task ID → last assignment time (prevents reassignment)\n}\n```\n\n**Key configuration:**\n- `MaxConcurrent`: how many host runs to keep active (default 1)\n- `StaggerDelay`: delay between launching consecutive runs\n- `DedupTimeout`: how long to suppress reassignment (default 5 min)\n\n**Loop algorithm** (`loop.run()`):\n1. **Fill slots**: While `inFlight < MaxConcurrent`:\n   - Check active host runs from store\n   - Optional: pick a task ID from `TaskAssigner` (with dedup filtering)\n   - Launch a new `Runner` goroutine\n2. **Wait for completions**: Listen on `completions` channel\n   - If succeeded: immediately try to fill slots again (no backoff)\n   - If failed: back off for `idlePollInterval` (30s) before retry\n3. **No tasks**: If task assigner returns no tasks, back off\n\n**Polling intervals:**\n- `idlePollInterval = 30s` (wait when no work available)\n- `capacityPollInterval = 5s` (wait when at capacity)\n- `defaultDedupTimeout = 5m` (task dedup window)\n\n---\n\n### Host Workflow Executor\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`\n\nThe `Executor` implements `engine.StepExecutor` for host workflow steps:\n\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n    ProjectDir    string\n    MainDir       string              // main branch worktree dir\n    Dispatcher    RunDispatcher        // dispatches container workflows\n    Store         ports.RunStore\n    OutputDir     string               // .cloche/<run-id>/output\n    Wires         []domain.Wire\n    HostRunID     string               // parent host run ID\n    AgentCommands []string             // fallback agent command chain\n    AgentArgs     []string\n    TaskID        string               // daemon-assigned task ID\n}\n```\n\n**Step execution by type:**\n\n1. **Script step** (`run` config key)\n   - Executes shell command via `exec.Command`\n   - Exit 0 → `success`; non-zero → `fail` (or look for result marker in output)\n   - Environment: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, plus output mappings\n   - Output written to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n\n2. **Workflow step** (`workflow_name` config key)\n   - Reads prompt from previous step's output (or `prompt_step` override)\n   - Calls `Dispatcher.RunWorkflow()` → returns child run ID\n   - Links child run to parent via `ParentRunID`\n   - **Polls** the store (2s interval) until child run reaches terminal state\n   - Child's `succeeded` → `success`; `failed`/`cancelled` → `fail`\n\n3. **Agent step** (`prompt` config key)\n   - Uses prompt adapter (at `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/`)\n   - Reads previous step output as prompt\n   - Invokes agent command on host\n   - Output captured and stored\n\n**Key helper functions:**\n- `resolveOutputMappings()`: extracts values from previous step output using JSON paths\n- `waitForRun()`: polls store until run is terminal\n- `findPrevOutput()`: locates previous step output for data flow\n- `stepOutputPath()`: returns file path for step output\n- `MainWorktreeDir()`: finds the main git worktree (for script execution context)\n\n---\n\n### Host Workflow Runner\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`\n\nThe `Runner` is the entry point for executing host workflows:\n\n```go\ntype Runner struct {\n    Dispatcher RunDispatcher          // to dispatch container workflows\n    Store      ports.RunStore\n    TaskID     string                 // optional task ID from daemon loop\n}\n\n// Run parses .cloche/host.cloche and executes the \"main\" workflow\nfunc (r *Runner) Run(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) (*RunResult, error)\n\n// RunWithID allows specifying a custom run ID\nfunc (r *Runner) RunWithID(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, runID string) (*RunResult, error)\n```\n\n**Execution flow:**\n1. Read `.cloche/host.cloche`\n2. Parse with `dsl.ParseForHost()` → validates as host workflow\n3. Verify workflow name is `\"main\"`\n4. Create output directory: `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n5. Create `domain.Run` record and persist to store\n6. Create an `Executor` and pass to `engine.New()`\n7. Run the workflow through the execution engine\n8. Persist final state to store\n\n**Status handler** (`hostStatusHandler`):\n- Logs step start/complete events\n- Updates `domain.Run` with step execution details\n- Called by the execution engine at key points\n\n---\n\n### Workflow Execution Engine\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go`\n\nThe `Engine` is workflow-agnostic and drives step execution:\n\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n    executor       StepExecutor        // host executor or container executor\n    status         StatusHandler       // callback interface for events\n    maxSteps       int                 // default 1000\n    defaultTimeout time.Duration       // default 30 min per step\n}\n\n// Run executes a workflow, returns terminal domain.Run or error\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx context.Context, wf *domain.Workflow) (*domain.Run, error)\n```\n\n**Algorithm:**\n1. Validate workflow (all results wired, all steps reachable)\n2. Launch entry step in a goroutine\n3. **Main event loop**: listen for step completions\n   - Validate result is declared\n   - Record completion in `domain.Run`\n   - Process wiring: get next targets via `wf.NextSteps(stepName, result)`\n   - Fanout: launch all target steps in parallel\n   - Handle `done` (success) and `abort` (fail) terminals\n   - Check `Collect` conditions (fanin: merge multiple branches)\n4. When all branches complete → determine final state\n\n**Collects** (fanin):\n- `CollectAll`: fire when ALL conditions are satisfied\n- `CollectAny`: fire when ANY condition is satisfied\n- Can target a step or terminal (`done`/`abort`)\n\n**Step timeout:**\n- Read from `step.Config[\"timeout\"]`\n- Fallback to engine's `defaultTimeout` (30 min)\n- Applied per step via `context.WithTimeout()`\n\n---\n\n### Daemon Integration\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\n**Startup flow:**\n1. Load global config (`~/.config/cloche/config`)\n2. Initialize SQLite store\n3. **Sweep stale runs** from previous daemon crash\n4. Initialize container runtime (Docker or local)\n5. Create gRPC server with:\n   - Store\n   - Container runtime\n   - Default image\n   - Log broadcaster\n   - Evolution trigger (optional)\n6. Call `autoRunActiveProjects()` for each project with `active: true` in config\n   - Launches a `Runner` in a goroutine for each active project's host workflow\n7. Listen on gRPC socket (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n\n**gRPC Server** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`):\n- `RunWorkflow(req)`: Dispatch a container workflow\n  - Generate unique run ID\n  - Write prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (if provided)\n  - Persist `domain.Run` to store\n  - Launch container **in background** (returns immediately)\n  - Container tracks completion asynchronously\n- Maintains `loops` map: `project_dir → *host.Loop`\n\n**Container workflow dispatch:**\n- `launchAndTrack()` runs in background goroutine\n- Ensures image is up-to-date (optional `ImageEnsurer`)\n- Calls `container.Start()` → container ID\n- Attaches to container output (JSON-lines status messages)\n- Tracks container exit status\n- Extracts results to git branches\n- Updates `domain.Run` state\n\n---\n\n### DSL Parsing\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go`\n\n**Workflow DSL format:**\n```\nworkflow \"name\" {\n  step step-name {\n    run = \"shell command\"               # OR\n    prompt = file(\"path/to/prompt\")     # OR\n    workflow_name = \"container-wf\"      # host.cloche only\n    results = [success, fail, ...]\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    timeout = \"10m\"\n  }\n\n  # Wiring (fan-out)\n  source-step:result -> target-step\n  source-step:result -> done\n  source-step:result -> abort\n\n  # Collect (fan-in)\n  collect all(step1:result1, step2:result2) -> target-step\n  collect any(step1:result1, step2:result2) -> target-step\n\n  # Workflow-level config\n  container {\n    image = \"my-image:latest\"\n  }\n\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n    agent_args = \"--model opus\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Step type inference:**\n- Presence of `run` key → `StepTypeScript`\n- Presence of `prompt` key → `StepTypeAgent`\n- Presence of `workflow_name` key → `StepTypeWorkflow` (host.cloche only)\n\n**Parser validation:**\n- Every result must be wired (via `Wire` or `Collect`)\n- Every step must be reachable from entry step\n- No duplicate env var mappings in wires\n- Location-based validation: `workflow_name` disallowed in container workflows\n\n---\n\n### Ports (Interfaces)\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/ports/`\n\n**`ports.RunStore`** — Persist run records\n- `CreateRun()`, `GetRun()`, `UpdateRun()`, `DeleteRun()`\n- `ListRuns()`, `ListRunsByProject()`, `ListProjects()`\n- `ListChildRuns()` (for parent-child relationships)\n\n**`ports.CaptureStore`** — Persist step execution details\n- `SaveCapture()`, `GetCaptures()`\n\n**`ports.ContainerRuntime`** — Manage containers\n- `Start()`, `Stop()`, `Wait()`, `Inspect()`\n- `AttachOutput()`, `CopyFrom()`, `Logs()`, `Remove()`\n- Optional: `ImageEnsurer.EnsureImage()`\n\n**`ports.LogStore`** — Index extracted log files\n- `SaveLogFile()`, `GetLogFiles()`, `GetLogFilesByStep()`, `GetLogFileByType()`\n\n---\n\n### Flow: Container Workflow Dispatch\n\n**When host executor runs a `workflow_name` step:**\n\n1. Host executor calls `Dispatcher.RunWorkflow(ctx, RunWorkflowRequest)`\n2. gRPC server handler:\n   - Generates unique run ID (workflow-specific format)\n   - Writes prompt to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Creates `domain.Run` record in store\n   - Launches `launchAndTrack()` in background\n3. `launchAndTrack()`:\n   - Ensures image is built\n   - Calls `container.Start()` → container ID\n   - Updates `domain.Run` to running state\n   - Calls `trackRun()` to monitor container\n4. `trackRun()`:\n   - Attaches to container stdout (JSON-lines protocol)\n   - Parses step execution events\n   - Updates `domain.Run` with step completions\n   - On exit: copies results to git branches\n   - Updates final run state\n5. Host executor polls via `waitForRun()`:\n   - Queries store every 2 seconds\n   - Returns when child run reaches terminal state\n   - Maps `succeeded` → `success`, `failed`/`cancelled` → `fail`\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon entrypoint, initialization, auto-run active projects |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` | Orchestration loop: maintains max concurrent runs |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow entry point, parsing, execution |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Step executor for host workflows (script, workflow, agent) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` | `Task` model and `TaskAssigner` interface |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Generic workflow execution engine, wiring/collect logic |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | `Workflow`, `Step`, `Wire`, `Collect`, `OutputMapping` types |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | `Run`, `StepExecution`, run state management |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/namegen.go` | Human-readable run ID generation |\n| `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` | Workflow DSL parsing |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC server, container dispatch, tracking |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | Interfaces: `RunStore`, `CaptureStore`, `LogStore`, `EvolutionStore` |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/container.go` | `ContainerRuntime`, `ContainerConfig`, `ImageEnsurer` |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/agent.go` | `AgentAdapter` interface |\n\n---\n\n### Design Document\n\nSee `/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-host-workflow-design.md` for the comprehensive design of host workflows."}],"totalDurationMs":79019,"totalTokens":59803,"totalToolUseCount":32,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":678,"cache_read_input_tokens":55034,"output_tokens":4091,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":678},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
