{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_0142nYfTCyLANGycDEiP6Zsi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. Task model (`internal/host/task.go`)\n- Added `Status` field (open/closed/in-progress) and `Metadata` field to `Task` struct\n- Added `TaskStatus` type constants\n- Added `Task.IsOpen()` method (backward-compatible: empty status = open)\n- Added `ParseTasksJSONL()` function that parses JSONL-formatted task output (one JSON object per line)\n\n### 2. DSL parser (`internal/dsl/parser.go`)\n- Added `ParseAllForHost()` function that parses host.cloche files containing multiple workflows, returning `map[string]*domain.Workflow`\n- Validates duplicate workflow names and empty files\n\n### 3. Runner (`internal/host/runner.go`)\n- Added `RunNamed(ctx, projectDir, workflowName)` method to run any named workflow from host.cloche\n- Added `ExtraEnv` field for passing additional env vars (used by finalize phase for `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME`, `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID`)\n- Added `OutputDir` to `RunResult` so the loop can read step outputs (e.g. list-tasks JSONL)\n- Refactored `Run`/`RunWithID` to use internal `runNamedWorkflow()` which calls `ParseAllForHost`\n\n### 4. Executor (`internal/host/executor.go`)\n- Added `ExtraEnv` field, propagated to script step environment\n\n### 5. Loop (`internal/host/loop.go`)\n- Added `NewPhaseLoop()` constructor for three-phase orchestration with `ListTasksFunc`, `MainFunc`, `FinalizeFunc`\n- `runPhased()` implements: list-tasks → pick open tasks (with dedup) → main → finalize\n- Finalize runs on **both success and failure** of main\n- Original `NewLoop()` and `runLegacy()` preserved for backward compatibility\n- Added `ReadListTasksOutput()` helper to read JSONL from workflow output directory\n\n### 6. gRPC server (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`)\n- `EnableLoop` now auto-detects three-phase mode by checking if host.cloche contains a `list-tasks` workflow\n- `createPhaseLoop()` wires up list-tasks → main → finalize using `Runner.RunNamed()`\n- Finalize receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` env vars\n- Falls back to legacy single-function mode when no list-tasks workflow exists\n\n### Tests Added\n- JSONL parsing: basic, metadata, empty lines, error handling, all statuses\n- `Task.IsOpen()`: all status variants\n- `ParseAllForHost`: single, multiple, duplicate names, empty, location validation\n- `RunNamed`: main, multi-workflow, not-found error\n- `ExtraEnv`: executor-level and runner-level propagation\n- `ReadListTasksOutput`: basic, empty dir, picks latest file\n- Phase loop: basic flow, skips closed tasks, finalize on failure, no finalize, dedup filtering\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":379,"cache_read_input_tokens":148318,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":379},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"84afe276-0872-4aba-bc33-ed0e3777b6c9","uuid":"2a7c7580-2ccd-41a4-a02b-695c651e0e4e"}
